    Identifiable

    public class Agent
extends AbstractSkillContainer
    The definition of the notion of Agent in SARL. An agent is an autonomous entity having some intrinsic skills to realize the capacities it exhibits. An agent defines a context.

        Creates a new agent with a parent parentID and initialize the built-in capacity with the given provider.
        Parameters:
        provider - the provider of built-in capacities for this agent. If null, the builtin capacities will not be initialized.
